    Lean-Idiomatic Naming Compatibility Layer #

    Dot-notation aliases for all Allegro handle-based functions. Import Allegro.Compat (or just Allegro, which re-exports it) to use handle-centric names like display.width instead of Allegro.getDisplayWidth display.

    The original C-style names remain available this module only adds aliases.

    source
    @[inline]
    def Allegro.Display.destroy (d : Display) :
    IO Unit
    Equations
    • d.destroy = Allegro.destroyDisplay d
    Instances For
      source
      @[inline]
      def Allegro.Display.width (d : Display) :
      IO UInt32
      Equations

      Instances For
        source

        IO UInt32
        Equations
        • d.height = Allegro.getDisplayHeight d
        Instances For

          IO UInt32
          Equations
          • d.resize w h = Allegro.resizeDisplay d w h
